What you need to know:

Kenya Open Golf Limited’s Tournament Director Patrick Obath said: “I believe that the combined distribution channels that the European Tour and the PGA Tour will have (the TV rights) will benefit the country.”He said as far as golf is concerned, it will open up Kenya and that it will hopefully raise the ambition of the members of the Safari Tour - those in Kenya and beyond - because winning the Kenya Open will be a stepping stone to a bigger pond.